# Development Workflow

## TDD Cycle (Red-Green-Refactor)

Every new feature or module follows this cycle:

1. **Red**: Write a failing test that describes the expected behavior
2. **Green**: Write the minimum code to make the test pass
3. **Refactor**: Clean up the code while keeping tests green

Never write production code without a corresponding test. Tests are written FIRST.

## Build Order Reference

The project follows a phased build approach. Check `docs/DEVELOPMENT_GUIDE.md` for full details.

**Current Phase**: Foundation (project setup, database, navigation, theme, design system).

## Before Writing Code

1. Write the test file first (TDD)
2. Check `docs/DATABASE_SCHEMA.md` for table/column definitions
3. Check `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` for which layer the code belongs to
4. Check existing entities in `src/domain/entities/` before creating new ones
5. Check `src/shared/types/` for shared type definitions

## Clean Architecture File Placement

- [ ] Entity -> `src/domain/entities/` (named export, PascalCase.ts)
- [ ] Use Case -> `src/domain/usecases/` (named export, verb-noun.ts)
- [ ] Repository Interface -> `src/domain/repositories/` (named export, I{Name}Repository.ts)
- [ ] Repository Impl -> `src/data/repositories/` (named export, {Name}Repository.ts)
- [ ] DB Model -> `src/data/database/models/` (default export, PascalCase.ts)
- [ ] Mapper -> `src/data/mappers/` (named export, {name}-mapper.ts)
- [ ] Screen -> `src/presentation/screens/` (default export, PascalCaseScreen.tsx)
- [ ] Component -> `src/presentation/components/` (named export, PascalCase.tsx)
- [ ] Hook -> `src/presentation/hooks/` (named export, useCamelCase.ts)
- [ ] Store -> `src/presentation/stores/` (named export, useCamelCaseStore.ts)
- [ ] Service -> `src/infrastructure/{domain}/` (named export, kebab-case.ts)
- [ ] Utility -> `src/shared/utils/` (named export, kebab-case.ts)
- [ ] Type -> `src/shared/types/` (named export, kebab-case.ts)
- [ ] Test -> `__tests__/` mirroring src structure

## Amounts Are Always Cents

All monetary values throughout the codebase are stored and operated on as **integer cents**.
- Display: `amountCents / 100` with `Intl.NumberFormat`
- Input: `Math.round(parseFloat(input) * 100)`
- Conversion: `Math.round((amountCents / fromRate) * toRate)`

## Text Conventions

Never use em dash characters. Use commas, periods, semicolons, or restructure sentences.
